<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1436,738,964]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,313,738,764]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Annotations:</emphasis>
The sole representative of the genus on the Canary Islands is morphologically closest to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Pipunculidae" genus="Chalarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zyginae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">C. zyginae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the female sex, but specimens are slightly larger in size and their frons is not as strongly narrowed (at narrowest point ~ 
<number box="[398,435,818,844]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="1.5">1.5</number>
times largest frontal facet instead of 1.0). Males should be addressed as 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Pipunculidae" genus="Chalarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="holosericeus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">C. holosericeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
agg., with php being slightly shorter than mtdp (
<figureCitation box="[781,867,858,884]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 11" captionStartId="9.[151,269,1761,1785]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,197,1734]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[155,1432,197,1735]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 11. Inner male genitalia (phallus). 7. C. decorus; 8. C. spurius; 9. C. zyginae; 10. C. griseus; 11. Chalarus sp. near zyginae. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/184952/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Fig. 
<number box="[836,867,858,884]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
). At this stage, no final decision can be made as to whether Canary 
<taxonomicName box="[375,484,898,923]" class="Insecta" family="Pipunculidae" genus="Chalarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[375,484,898,923]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Chalarus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be regarded as a distinct species or not, due to the lack of molecular data. For the time being it might be addressed as 
<taxonomicName box="[663,772,938,963]" class="Insecta" family="Pipunculidae" genus="Chalarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[663,772,938,963]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Chalarus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. near 
<taxonomicName box="[877,967,938,963]" class="Insecta" family="Pipunculidae" genus="Chalarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zyginae">
<emphasis box="[877,967,938,963]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">zyginae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
